•	GitHub Desktop (GUI) Workflow:
•	=============================
•	Clone repo
o	From GitHub Desktop: File → Clone Repository or use the clone URL.
•	Create a new branch
o	Top panel → Current Branch → New Branch.
•	Make changes to code
o	Edit files locally in your code editor.
•	Stage the changes
o	GitHub Desktop detects changes.
•	Use the + button to stage selected files.
o	Commit with message
•	Enter a message like [JIRA-1234] Fixed XYZ → Click Commit to [branch name].
o	Push the changes
o	Click Publish branch (if first time), or Push origin (if already published).
o	Create Pull Request (PR)
•	Go to GitHub web UI → Navigate to the branch → Click “Compare & pull request”.
o	Add reviewers, test details
o	Enter test details, reviewers, and PR description → Click Create pull request.
o	Merge after review
•	Once approved → Click Merge Pull Request → Optionally delete branch.
